args: Whew! All right, that's all of them.\nLet's meet up with the others.
You were a huge help today, Louise.\nThank you.
(I don't feel like a big sister when I'm with\nhim. It's like I can just be who I am\nnaturally.)
Thank you for that. It seems I let my\nguard down.
Not exactly my finest hour, I fear.
Don't worry about it. It's only natural that\nwe'd help each other out.
You ARE a curious fellow, aren't you?
You just accept all of my flaws without\nany judgment whatsoever.
I've always been the one who had to\naccept flaws, so this feels rather odd.
Perhaps this is what it's like to have an\nolder brother.
You and Lowen really have been alone\nin your own little world, huh?
Perhaps these new feelings are a sign\nthat you've taken a step into a much\nlarger world.
You might be right. I've certainly never\nexperienced such a feeling before.
What? No! I was merely trying to think of\nan example to explain how I felt.
Heh. I get it. Although now that you\nmention it, I've also been having\na strange feeling lately.

When I see you confused about who you
are—and yet trying so hard to figure it
out—it makes me want to stop whatever
I'm doing and help you.
Maybe that's the big brother vibe you've\nbeen getting.
D-don't tease your elders like that!
I'm not teasing. Also, this kind of thing\nisn't really about age.
You're searching for a new way to live,\nand it's okay to rely on someone else for\nhelp—even if they happen to be younger.
Unless you don't want to rely on me,\nin which case I totally underst—
Ugh! Enough! I didn't mean to call you\nmy big brother!
And I am CERTAINLY not relying on you!
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to upset you.
I'm not upset! It's just... I mean... Ugh.
I'm sorry. I WAS angry there for a moment,\nalthough I didn't intend to be.
Oh, you were just being a contrarian, huh.
Go on, make fun. It's just...hard for me to\nbe open with my feelings.
Haha. That sort of trait is probably what\nmakes me feel the need to help you.
Louise, if you're up for it... I'd like it\nif you can be more open with me.
If there's something troubling you, I want\nyou to know you can rely on me.
I'd be happy if you did that.
I feel like, with you, I actually can...
